cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.IR 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing tasks such as sentiment classification, part-of-speech tagging, and document classification. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper discusses machine learning models and parameter tuning. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is less likely but still possible as the J-K-fold CV method can be applied to image classification tasks as well. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also possible as the paper deals with machine learning models and performance estimation. 
- cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses document classification, which is a subfield of information retrieval.
